main event: On the night of July 18, 1963, a witness observed a brilliantly luminous object traveling at high speed over Key West, Florida.
interesting points: The object was silent and had no blinking or running lights., The witness described the object as being the size of the full moon and said it left a whitish cloud of smoke behind., The object appeared to be drifting or towing something similar in size., The witness noted that the object's disappearance was at a speed impossible for known aircraft., Another report from July 19 observed a similar object with similar characteristics.
witness description: The witness reported the sighting from their home on Saddle Bunch Key, indicating it was at a great distance.
